

Term Deposit Calculator

This is a simple command-line application that calculates the final balance of a term deposit based on user-provided inputs such as start deposit amount, interest rate, investment term, and interest paid frequency.

How to Use

Installation
Make sure you have Python installed on your system. If not, you can download and install it from Python's official website.
Running the Program
Save the provided Python script (term_deposit_calculator.py) to your computer.
Open your terminal or command prompt.
Navigate to the directory where the script is saved using the cd command.
Run the script by typing python term_deposit_calculator.py and pressing Enter.
Input Information
Follow the prompts in the terminal to input the start deposit amount, interest rate, investment term, and interest paid frequency.
View Output
After providing the required inputs, the program will calculate the final balance of the term deposit and display it in the terminal.
Repeat as Necessary
You can run the program multiple times with different inputs to calculate different scenarios.
Requirements

Python 3.x
